SIMPLE: sputter
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sputter
<hw>Sput"ter</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ucr⟧t"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sputtered</conjf>
<pr>(-t⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sputtering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From the root of
<ets>spout</ets> or <ets>spit</ets> to eject from the mouth. Cf.
<er>Splutter</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To spit, or to emit saliva
from the mouth in small, scattered portions, as in rapid
speaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter words hastily and indistinctly; to speak so
rapidly as to emit saliva.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They could neither of them speak their rage, and so fell a
<qex>sputtering</qex> at one another, like two roasting apples.</q>
<rj><qau>Congreve.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To throw out anything, as little jets of steam, with
a noise like that made by one sputtering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like the green wood . . . <qex>sputtering</qex> in the flame.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sputter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sputter
<hw>Sput"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To spit out hastily by quick,
successive efforts, with a spluttering sound; to utter hastily and
confusedly, without control over the organs of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the midst of caresses, and without the least pretended
incitement, to <qex>sputter</qex> out the basest accusations.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sputter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sputter
<hw>Sput"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Moist matter thrown out in small
detached particles; also, confused and hasty speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sputterer</ent>⟦br⟧
